design:
Deep useUploadTunkin hook, form/router/cache injected via wrapper.

INTERFACE
  type UploadPhase = "idle"|"probing"|"confirming"|"uploading"|"done"|"error";
  type UploadResult =
    | { ok: true }
    | { ok: false; reason: "probe-failed"|"upload-failed"|"cancelled"; error?: Error };
  interface UseUploadTunkinOptions {
    confirmOverwrite: (periode: string) => Promise<boolean>;
    onSuccess?: () => void;
  }
  interface UseUploadTunkin {
    phase: UploadPhase;
    error: Error | null;
    submit: (values: { file: File; periode: string }) => Promise<UploadResult>;
  }

LAYERS
1. useUploadTunkin (hook) — policy only: probe via cekExistingTunkin, if is_exist call confirmOverwrite, if confirmed call doUpload. Transition phase along the way. Returns discriminated UploadResult so callers can await + toast specific reasons. No useForm, no useSearchParams, no useQueryClient inside.
2. <UploadTunkinDialog> (wrapper component, adapted from current src/components/form/form-dialog.tsx) — owns useForm(UploadTunkinSchema), owns AlertDialog state for overwrite-confirm and resolves the promise from button clicks, owns useSearchParams + queryClient.invalidateQueries(["tunkin", params.toString()]) in onSuccess.
3. doUpload action — shrinks to raw POST multipart adapter (no try/catch reshaping after q7s lands).

POLICY DECISIONS (from grilling)
- Overwrite UX: controlled AlertDialog (not window.confirm). Periode visible in dialog body.
- Probe failure: BLOCKING. submit resolves { ok: false, reason: "probe-failed" }. UI shows toast; user cannot proceed. Coordinate with BE team for Probe SLA.
- Probe→Upload race (silent overwrite if another user uploads between probe and POST): KNOWN LIMITATION. Will coordinate with BE team — preferred fix is 409 from /tunkin/upload when periode appeared after the caller-driven probe window. Not blocking this issue.
- form-agnostic hook (H2): wrapper component owns form + Zod. Hook only sees { file, periode }.
- query-cache-agnostic hook (G2): wrapper invalidates in onSuccess. Hook does not import @tanstack/react-query.

Single ZodField<T> module with discriminated 'variant' prop replaces InputZod/BulanZod/TahunZod/InputFileZod.

Shape:
  type ZodFieldProps<T> = {
    id: Path<T>; form: UseFormReturn<T>; label?: string; className?: string;
  } & (
    | { variant: 'text'; inputType?: 'text'|'number'|'float'|'email'|'password'; readonly?: boolean }
    | { variant: 'select'; options: { value: string; label?: string }[]; placeholder?: string }
    | { variant: 'file'; accept?: string }
  );

Internals: one Controller, one Field/FieldLabel/FieldError shell. Variant switch picks inner control (Input | Select | Input type=file). Number/float coerce via Number() in onChange; file extracts files?[0].

Domain options export to src/tipes/options.ts: BULAN_OPTIONS (12 months Jan-Des), TAHUN_OPTIONS (current year - 4 years, computed at module load). Callers pass these as the options prop.

Dropped:
  - 'hidden' inputType variant (no caller uses it; grep confirmed).
  - phantom fileRef: UseFormRegisterReturn from InputFileZodProps (never read).
  - memo wrappers BulanItem/TahunItem (premature optimization; SelectItem is cheap).
  - inconsistent error rendering: BulanZod/TahunZod currently SILENTLY DROP FieldError. ZodField always renders FieldError when fieldState.invalid. This fixes a latent bug masked as duplication.

Call site migration:
  src/app/login/login-form.tsx: InputZod -> ZodField variant='text'
  src/app/dashboard/form-dialog.tsx:
    TahunZod      -> ZodField variant='select' options={TAHUN_OPTIONS}
    BulanZod      -> ZodField variant='select' options={BULAN_OPTIONS}
    InputFileZod  -> ZodField variant='file' accept='.xlsx,.xls'

